  </div>

  <div class="clear"></div>
</div>

    </div>
  </div>
    <div class="elementListBrownSeparator"></div>



  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2357610314" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2357610314" />
    <a title="Alicia Harlington" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/76206473-alicia-harlington"><img alt="Alicia Harlington" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2357610314?book_show_action=true">Apr 10, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Alicia Harlington" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Alicia Harlington" href="/user/show/76206473-alicia-harlington">Alicia Harlington</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/76206473-alicia-harlington?shelf=children-s-books">children-s-books</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2357610314" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12857911781489768615">The Adventures of Huckleberry Finn written by Mark Twain, even though it is a classic children&apos;s book, it was not my cup of tea. Which is why I did rate it a two out of five stars. I feel as though that this book is a lot for children to handle, especially younger ones just because they might not fully understand what Mark Twain is trying to say. He uses racism and slavery in such a way that I personally feel is too old for the younger crowd. This book is way too sophisticated for young readers </span>
  <span id="freeText12857911781489768615" style="display:none">The Adventures of Huckleberry Finn written by Mark Twain, even though it is a classic children's book, it was not my cup of tea. Which is why I did rate it a two out of five stars. I feel as though that this book is a lot for children to handle, especially younger ones just because they might not fully understand what Mark Twain is trying to say. He uses racism and slavery in such a way that I personally feel is too old for the younger crowd. This book is way too sophisticated for young readers and would definitely need some assistance with parents. On the other hand, I do think that this book is a good starting point for children to ask questions to their parents about some difficult topics but other than that I did not enjoy this book. Last but not least there is violence and many deaths that do include two children which also could be rough for children to read. Would recommend only to the older crowd.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12857911781489768615" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


